This document describes the Beluga source code, including a
description of the source code structure and a description of the
Beluga project.

*      [Structure](#01)

*      [Project Description](#02)

       *        [Contextual Modal Type Theory](#03)


Structure <a id="01"/>
=========


beluga
------

    INSTALL.text        Compilation and installation instructions
    README.text         Current file
    STYLE.text          Comments on stylistic conventions
    TODO.text           List of tasks to be completed


doc
---

Various papers describing Contextual Modal Type Theory.


ocaml-notes
-----------

Many of the programmers on this project were experienced with SML but
not Ocaml.  `ocaml-notes` contains information relevant such people.


src
---

    Makefile            make driver for ocamlbuild
    _tags               ocamlbuild configuration for local directory
    beluga.mltop        Beluga-specific toplevel target
    core.mlpack         Target to pack core/* into Target module
    frontend.mlpack     Target to pack frontend/* into Frontend module
    interpreter.mlpack  Target to pack interperter/* into Interpreter module
    myocamlbuild.ml     Custom ocamlbuild plugin


core
----

    _tags               ocamlbuild configuration for local directory
    config.ml           State configuration for Core
    core.odocl          Target to generate Core documentation
    gensym.ml           Unique symbol generation
    gensym.mli          ...
    id.ml               Identifiers, used for variables, constants, etc.
    id.mli              ...
    normalize.ml        Normalization
    normalize.mli       ...
    store.ml            Variable store, maps ids to variable information
    store.mli           ...
    syntax.ml           Syntax for the LF and computation layer of Beluga
    typecheck.ml        Typechecking
    typecheck.mli       ...



frontend
--------

    _tags               ocamlbuild configuration for local directories
    frontend.odocl      Target to generate Frontend documentation
    lexer.ml            Beluga lexer
    lexer.mli           ...
    parser.ml           Beluga parser
    token.ml            Tokens for lexing



interpreter
-----------

    _tags               ocamlbuild configuration for local directories
    interpreter.odocl   Target to generate Interpreter documentation


tools
-----



